      "description": "No root cause analysis distinguishes between 'fields not projected in SQL' versus 'fields not indexed in PG'. PGSearchAdapter might simply need a SELECT clause update, or the PG index might lack the column entirely. Proposing normalization without this analysis risks selecting the wrong fix (expensive reindexing vs cheap projection).",
      "suggested_fix": "Add a mandatory field coverage audit: compare the grader's required field list against (a) the PG table schema and (b) the PGSearchAdapter SQL projection. Document whether the gap is in the storage layer or the adapter layer."
